


Project Overview (Start your explanation like this)
This project is called Trade File Processing and Management Service.
It is a Spring Boot multi-module backend application designed to process daily trade files, store the data in a database, and provide REST APIs to manage those files.
The system uses Spring Batch to process large files, Spring Security with JWT to secure APIs, and OpenAPI (Swagger) for API documentation.
2. Overall Flow of the System
Explain the system in this simple flow.
Trade File
↓
Spring Batch processes the file
↓
Data stored in MySQL staging tables
↓
Metadata stored (file name, status, records etc.)
↓
REST APIs allow users to manage records
↓
JWT authentication secures APIs
↓
Swagger provides API documentation
3. Multi-Module Backend Architecture
This project follows a multi-module Maven architecture.
Instead of putting everything in one project, the application is divided into separate modules, each responsible for a specific function.
Modules used in the project:
Parent Module
API Module
Service Module
DAO Module
Model Module
Batch Module
Security Module
This separation makes the system clean, scalable, and easy to maintain.
4. Parent Module
Explanation you can say:
The Parent Module is the root project that manages all submodules.
Responsibilities:
Manages dependencies
Defines common configurations
Builds all modules together
Example structure
Copy code

trade-file-processing-parent
│
├── api-module
├── service-module
├── dao-module
├── model-module
├── batch-module
└── security-module
The parent pom.xml controls all modules.
5. API Module (Controller Layer)
Explanation:
The API Module exposes REST endpoints which clients or frontend applications use to interact with the system.
Responsibilities:
Receive HTTP requests
Validate input
Call service layer
Return response
Example APIs:
Search File Records
Update File Status
Delete File Record
Archive File Record
Example endpoints
GET /files/search
PUT /files/{id}/status
DELETE /files/{id}
POST /files/{id}/archive
Structure
Copy code

api-module
└── controller
     └── FileLoadController.java
6. Service Module (Business Logic Layer)
Explanation:
The Service Module contains the business logic of the application.
It acts as a bridge between the controller layer and database layer.
Responsibilities:
Implement business rules
Process data
Validate logic
Call DAO layer
Example services
FileLoadService
SearchService
ArchiveService
StatusService
Flow
Controller → Service → DAO
